@alasky17 Thank you for the clarification, to be safe though I'll check back in a few weeks since some reports show that _some_ bans were quite delayed.

@funkerwolf I've seen some blame the ReFS bans on Ricochet but as _this_ game doesn't use Ricochet, I'm inclined to believe that this is an engine-level bug that originated either with CW or MW19. Maybe there's some sort of integrity check that uses some call specific to NTFS that isn't present in Linux filesystems (and supported in Wine) or MS's ReFS?

I'm also curious if a ban would still occur if the BTRFS Windows driver was used, but that would probably be a waste of $20-$60. It's a shame that Activision is being so vague.
